title: Grateful Dead Live at State Fairgrounds on 1980-09-06
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi DR-2 > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 2496
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Sugaree, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed, Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, Far From Me, Little Red Rooster, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Promised Land

Set 2

Shakedown Street, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance, Althea, Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> The Wheel-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band-> Sugar Magnolia, E:One More Saturday Night-> E: Brokedown Palace

Roy Bucanan then Levon Helm Opened

reviews.review_text: The best so far! This recording of a smokin' show requires no EQing whatsoever to sound perfect. It beats the more recent Bob Morris recording, and even beats the redoubtable Charlie Miller version. They were in a funky mood this night: Stranger AND Shakedown in the same show! Love that Mutron envelope filter! No wonder Weir had to ask everybody to take a step back: I'd be up there gettin' squeezed and lovin' it!
80's dead Really a kick ass show overall.Jerry is Smokin.love the set list.one of my favorite shows from the 80's
